rComments: She obviously doesn't want to teach, does not care to answer emails, posts powerpoints whenever she wants, does not follow original syllabus. avoid at all costs. If you genuinely want to learn don't take a class with her. She doesn't seem to care about her student at all. One of the worst professors i've ever had in my 3 years at this university.

She doesnt answer her e-mails. She reads the slides out loud and adds very few extra details. She didnt provide us the criteria grading and then she was a tough grader (??). Her exams were pretty straight forward, get your notes and youll get a good grade. Overall, bad experience, she gives the impression that she doesnt want to be teaching.

Avoid at all cost. Asks to be unmute for the final which does not make sense. Refuse to give grading criteria even if its written in the syllabus. The material for the class is having lists of words, no explanation.

Avoid if you can ! She doesn't want to teach and it's easy to feel it. Asynchronous classes but she posts the PPT at random times, refuse to post the grading criteria for the group project (???). Also, she reads the PPT.
